				<div class="page-paragraph_block">
					<p>As one of the biggest cancer treatment drugs on the market, it was necessary for the web experience of the consumer-facing <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180823174426/https://www.keytruda.com/" target="_blank">Keytruda.com</a> to be updated to modern standards with iteration and flexibility in mind. The <b>existing experience was not responsive nor accessible, had confusing navigation menus, and wasn’t built with future expansion in mind</b>. The brand had also quickly evolved since 2017 when this version was launched, with an ever expanding list of indications (now over 25), countless projects evolving the visual style, and a growing agency team (now over 120 members).</p>
					<p>These problems were the focus when I first joined the Merck team at Digitas Health and began working on the redesign of Keytruda.com with a large team that included an art director, another designer, three UX experts, and multiple project managers, copywriters, and developers. I had joined after preliminary UX research had been completed, early designs had been explored and a general look and feel had been approved by the client team, and  <b>with my past experiences I was able to perfectly fill the role of creating and maintaining the design system and component library</b>.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>


