		</div>

		<div class="grid align-center">
			<div class="col-7_lg-8_sm-10_xs-12">
				<div class="page-paragraph_block">
					<p>At a technical level, much of my early work on this project was organizing the existing work completed on the project, such as typeface, colors and other base-level elements, into logical groups, <b>establishing a naming convention, and creating all of the necessary design tokens needed to establish the visual consistency</b> of the web pages and components. </p>
					<p>Leveraging Sketch, and it’s Symbol Library features, I was then able to <b>explore, design and iterate the necessary components</b> working alongside a creative director and a copywriter, with continued input from our UX experts to ensure each element <b>met the necessary standards and requirements from usability, brand style, and content</b>. These components included a set of extensively reworked and redesigning data visualization components, user-friendly global navigation, content callouts and CTAs, brand-infused page heroes, new visual structure for the legally-required safety information elements, and new UX-focused sign up forms & fields.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>	
	</section>
	


