					<p>Other projects I worked on related to this style library:</p>
					<p><a href="https://www.keytrudalenvima.com/advanced-endometrial-cancer/" target="_blank"><b>Keytruda + Lenvima</a> is a website based off of the KEY Style Library which is used to promote a different use of the Keytruda immunotherapy</b>. While built off of the existing groundwork and guidelines, this project had its own challenges as we had to include standards and styles from another brand and meet an appropriate balance between the two, as well as collaborate with a new group of stakeholders. This involved creating new components, alternate versions of existing elements and tackling new UX challenges.</p>

					<p><a href="https://www.keytruda.com/getting-started/" target="_blank"><b>Digital Quick Start Guide</a> is a short and direct summary of the most important content found on the Keytruda site.</b> One of the first new pieces of content for the site, this project was a new UI and UX challenge that allowed us to explore new ways to expand the style guide and test new ways to present user-friendly content.</p>

					<p><b>Keytruda Chatbot is a chatbot created to assist users on the website and help navigate them to the content they are searching for.</b> I was pulled in to help explore and iterate on a visual style for the chatbot UI that would follow the visual style of the site, while also keeping in line with the limitations of the pre-built software we were leveraging.</p>
